properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 5 at 3:30PM AKST until January 7 at 6:00AM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow. Total snow accumulation 3 to 5 inches.

* WHERE...Juneau, Douglas, Mendenhall Valley, and out the road.

* WHEN...Monday night.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow totals may vary significantly over
short distances. Higher amounts expected at Eaglecrest.
properties.instruction:
An advisory means that a potentially hazardous event is already
occurring or imminent. Driving may be hazardous and the Tuesday
morning commute may be adversely impacted.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM MONDAY TO 6 AM AKST TUESDAY
